  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">WASH response in Telkaif district (Doghat and Baqufa)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The L3 humanitarian crisis in Northern Iraq, instigated by ISIS&#x2019; capture of Mosul in June 2014 has destroyed homes, infrastructures, and economies and caused displacement, violence, loss of lives and livelihoods, social tensions, strained resources and uncertainty. 
Al Qosh sub-district (Telkaif district, Ninevah Governorate) was partly affected by ISIS presence and some of its unaffected areas have been refuge for many IDPs, mostly members of Christian and Yezidi minorities. After retaken of Telkaif district by Iraqi and Pesmerga forces, some IDPs slowly started to return to their homes. It happened mostly in Teleskuf city and Baqufa. Protection, electricity and water are the main conditions for return.  In some villages (Yezidi) close to Teleskuf city, the number of IDPs increased a need to improve water systems to enable access to water to the population. 
Lutheran World Federation Iraq (LWF) proposes project to reduce vulnerability of 4,200 internally displaced, returnees and local community members in Telkaif district (Al Qosh sub-district, Ninevah Governorate) through WASH response. The project targets various minority groups including Christians and Yazidis, 
The 6-month project includes activities covering two water projects:
1. Extending water supply system from Teleskuf water station to Baqufa village (4 km).
2. Extending water supply system in Doghat village (2 km)
The proposed action focuses on returnees, IDPs and host community members in Al Qosh sub-district</narrative>
  </description>
